17:05.344 --> 17:06.706
But his prominence

17:07.138 --> 17:15.069
was gained through the witness of the transformed lives spreading this news to others.

17:15.189 --> 17:17.733
See, that's a big difference.

17:19.916 --> 17:29.168
As you see, Jesus was not what anybody expected, and yet he was everything that everyone needed.

17:29.188 --> 17:36.338
I believe that Jesus is worth serving because he is not like

17:36.418 --> 17:37.440
any other king.

17:37.520 --> 17:41.265
He wasn't like the Caesars of the world.

17:41.365 --> 17:58.130
I believe the shepherds were rejoicing in praising God here in this story because they finally encountered a king, a God that noticed them, that included them.

17:59.266 --> 18:12.688
Now I've been following Jesus for a long time and man, one of the biggest lies that the enemy makes against us is making us think that all of this isn't for us.

18:14.151 --> 18:19.179
That we have to act a certain way, that we have to be of certain status, that we have to be perfect.

18:20.782 --> 18:23.346
But my favorite part of this message

18:23.618 --> 18:32.993
from the angels to them in this story is they say, I proclaim to you good news of great joy that will be for all the people.

18:34.115 --> 18:37.601
A savior was born for you.

18:37.621 --> 18:45.874
If you're new to this whole Christianity thing, I just want you to know that this is for you.

18:47.490 --> 18:56.667
