20:49.866 --> 21:05.906
Paul says this, he says, adopt this same attitude as that of Christ Jesus who existing in the form of God did not consider equality with God as something to be exploited.

21:07.234 --> 21:24.895
Instead, he emptied himself by assuming the form of a servant, taking on the likeness of humanity, and when he had come as a man, he humbled himself by becoming obedient to the point of death, even to death on a cross.

21:26.597 --> 21:34.226
For this reason, God's highly, God highly exalted him and gave him the name that is above every name,

21:34.690 --> 21:46.490
